### Phase 3: Anti-Backup Policy Implementation
dependencies: [2]

**Objective**: Prevent future backup file proliferation through .gitignore and pre-commit hook

**Complexity**: Low

Tasks:
- [ ] Create `.gitignore` in commands directory: `/home/benjamin/.config/.claude/commands/.gitignore`
  - [ ] Add pattern: `*.backup*`
  - [ ] Add pattern: `*.bak`
  - [ ] Add pattern: `*.phase-based*`
  - [ ] Add pattern: `*~`
  - [ ] Add comment explaining policy: "All version history managed via git"
- [ ] Create pre-commit hook: `/home/benjamin/.config/.git/hooks/pre-commit`
  - [ ] Check if hook already exists, preserve existing checks
  - [ ] Add backup file detection logic
  - [ ] Error message: "Use git commits for version control, not backup files"
  - [ ] Exit code 1 if backups detected
  - [ ] Make executable: `chmod +x .git/hooks/pre-commit`
- [ ] Test pre-commit hook
  - [ ] Create test backup: `touch .claude/commands/test.backup`
  - [ ] Attempt commit: `git add .claude/commands/test.backup && git commit -m "test"`
  - [ ] Verify rejection with clear error message
  - [ ] Remove test file: `rm .claude/commands/test.backup`
- [ ] Document policy in developer guide
  - [ ] Add section to `/home/benjamin/.config/.claude/docs/guides/command-development-guide.md`
  - [ ] Policy statement: "Commands directory MUST NOT contain backup files"
  - [ ] Rationale: Git provides complete version history
  - [ ] Recovery examples from git-recovery-guide.md
