## Testing Strategy

### Unit Testing
- Pre-commit hook functionality (create backup file, verify rejection)
- Git recovery examples (view/restore historical versions)
- Documentation validation script (README ↔ command-reference consistency)

### Integration Testing
- Complete workflow: backup removal → anti-backup policy → attempt re-creation → verify block
- Deprecation warnings display correctly when invoking deprecated commands
- All documentation cross-references resolve correctly

### Validation Testing
- Directory listing verification (before/after counts)
- Disk space measurement (before/after usage)
- Git history accessibility (deleted backup files recoverable)

### Regression Testing
- Run full test suite per CLAUDE.md protocols after each phase
- Verify no active commands broken by cleanup
- Verify documentation still builds/renders correctly

